an Conquest.","Breton: very rare variant of   Briant   (see   Briand  ) and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this.","History: The American poet William Cullen Bryant (1794–1878) came of a New England family, being descended from Stephen Bryant, who had settled in Plymouth Colony in 1632."]}]},{"name":"Guy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of a compound name starting with <i>witu</i> ‘wood’ or <i>wīt</i> ‘wide’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England. In Old French initial <i>w-</i> regularly became <i>gu-</i>. The usual Norman forms of the name were <i>Gy</i> or <i>Guido</i>. In medieval Latin the same name is found as <i>Wido</i>. It was a popular name among the Normans, enhanced no doubt by the romance of Guy of Warwick, recounting the exploits of a folk hero of the Crusades."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Guy De Bryon was born in 1272, in Burton, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir Guy De Bryon."},"et":{"1272–":"1272–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1316–Female":"1316–Surnud","1272–Female":"1272–Surnud","1316":"1316","about 1316":"umbes 1316","1272":"1272","1270":"1270","of Burton, Buckinghamshire, England.":"Burton, Hampshire, England","Burton, Buckingham, England, United Kingdom":"Burton, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1272–":"1272–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1316–Female":"1316–Kuollut","1272–Female":"1272–Kuollut","1316":"1316","about 1316":"noin 1316","1272":"1272","1270":"1270","of Burton, Buckinghamshire, England.":"Burton, Hampshire, England","Burton, Buckingham, England, United Kingdom":"Burton, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1272–":"1272–Décédée","1270–Male":"1270–Décédé","1316–Female":"1316–Décédée","1272–Female":"1272–Décédée","1316":"1316",